</strong> Time period</div><div><strong>B)</strong> Frequency</div><div><strong>C)</strong> Amplitude</div><div><strong>D)</strong> Displacement</div></div></div><div class=\"mcq-item\"><div class=\"mcq-question\"><strong>Q4.</strong> Which of the following is an example of simple harmonic motion?</div><div class=\"mcq-options\"><div><strong>A)</strong> Motion of a simple pendulum</div><div><strong>B)</strong> The motion of ceiling fan</div><div><strong>C)</strong> The spinning of the earth on its axis</div><div><strong>D)</strong> A bouncing ball on a floor</div></div></div><div class=\"mcq-item\"><div class=\"mcq-question\"><strong>Q5.</strong> The bending and spreading of waves around the sharp edges or corners of obstacles is called:</div><div class=\"mcq-options\"><div><strong>A)</strong> Refraction</div><div><strong>B)</strong> Reflection</div><div><strong>C)</strong> Diffraction</div><div><strong>D)</strong> None of these</div></div></div><div class=\"mcq-item\"><div class=\"mcq-question\"><strong>Q6.</strong> If the mass of the bob of pendulum is increased by a factor of 3, the period of pendulum motion will:</div><div class=\"mcq-options\"><div><strong>A)</strong> Be increased by a factor of 2</div><div><strong>B)</strong> Remain same</div><div><strong>C)</strong> Be decreased by a factor of 2</div><div><strong>D)</strong> Be decreased by a factor of 4</div></div></div><div class=\"mcq-item\"><div class=\"mcq-question\"><strong>Q7.</strong> A large ripple tank with a vibrator working at a frequency of 30 Hz produces 25 complete waves in a distance of 50 cm. The velocity of the wave is:</div><div class=\"mcq-options\"><div><strong>A)</strong> 53cms-1</div><div><strong>B)</strong> 60 cms-1</div><div><strong>C)</strong> 750 cms-1</div><div><strong>D)</strong> 1500 cms-1</div></div></div><div class=\"mcq-item\"><div class=\"mcq-question\"><strong>Q8.</strong> Transverse waves consists of ________</div><div class=\"mcq-options\"><div><strong>A)</strong> Crest</div><div><strong>B)</strong> Trough</div><div><strong>C)</strong> Both a and b</div><div><strong>D)</strong> None of these</div></div></div><div class=\"mcq-item\"><div class=\"mcq-question\"><strong>Q9.</strong> Which of the following characteristics of a wave is independent of the others:</div><div class=\"mcq-options\"><div><strong>A)</strong> Speed</div><div><strong>B)</strong> Frequency</div><div><strong>C)</strong> Amplitude</div><div><strong>D)</strong> Wavelength</div></div></div><div class=\"mcq-item\"><div class=\"mcq-question\"><strong>Q10.</strong> A wave on slinky spring with frequency 4Hz and wavelength of 0.4m has speed:</div><div class=\"mcq-options\"><div><strong>A)</strong> 1.9 m/s</div><div><strong>B)</strong> 1.6 m/s</div><div><strong>C)</strong> 1.1 m/s</div><div><strong>D)</strong> 0.9 m/s</div></div></div></div></div> \r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <!-- Short Questions Sections --> \r\n        <div id=\"short-long-section\">\r\n        <div class=\"section\"> \r\n            <textarea placeholder=\"Enter heading for Section 1\"></textarea> \r\n            <ol type=\"i\"><li><div class=\"question-row\"><div class=\"question-content\"><strong>i.</strong> <span class=\"q-text\">Define mechanical waves and electromagnetic waves.</span></div><div class=\"marks-container\"><input type=\"number\" value=\"2\" class=\"marks-input\" /></div></div><div class=\"action-buttons\"><button class=\"btn edit\" onclick=\"makeEditable(this)\">Edit</button></div></li><li><div class=\"question-row\"><div class=\"question-content\"><strong>ii.</strong> <span class=\"q-text\">Define diffraction of waves.</span></div><div class=\"marks-container\"><input type=\"number\" value=\"2\" class=\"marks-input\" /></div></div><div class=\"action-buttons\"><button class=\"btn edit\" onclick=\"makeEditable(this)\">Edit</button></div></li><li><div class=\"question-row\"><div class=\"question-content\"><strong>iii.</strong> <span class=\"q-text\">Define simple pendulum and write